00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:05,000
 if he could keep his promise and come into that space

252
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:08,000
 and be with that people,

253
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:11,000
 then there's no situation that you're in.

254
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:14,000
 There's no darkness that you're in.

255
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:20,000
 There's no shame that you can carry that's too shameful.

256
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:24,000
 There's no hurt beyond what he can step into.

257
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,000
 If he can enter a nation that would barely recognize him,

258
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:32,000
 he can step into your space today.

259
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:36,000
 He's come for the righteous, for the sinners.

260
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:39,000
 He's come for those who believe.

261
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:42,000
 He's faithful to those who don't yet believe.

262
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:47,000
 This is why Zachariah is singing and rejoicing,

263
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,000
 because you can find rest in this.

264
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,000
 You don't have to worry about,

265
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,000
 "Is God going to change his mind on me?

266
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,000
 Is God still going to love me? Is God still God?"

267
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:58,000
 He is faithful. He keeps his promise. He keeps his word.

268
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,000
 And that is why Zachariah sings,

269
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 "Praise be to the Lord, the God of Israel,

270
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:07,000
 because he has come to his people and redeemed them."

271
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:12,000
 God has kept his promise.

272
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:15,000
 Zachariah continues after explaining

273
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:18,000
 that God is worthy of praise because he keeps his word

274
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,000
 no matter what happens.

275
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 God keeps his word.

276
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,000
 He continues and lays out a second understanding

277
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,000
 of what rest could look like.

278
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,000
 Rest based off of the understanding

279
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:31,000
 that God has this mission that is massive.

280
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,000
 When you understand the mission of God,

281
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,000
 what he's up to in the world,

282
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:38,000
 it can bring you to rest.

283
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,000
 And it reads like this,

284
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:43,000
 "Salvation from our enemies,

285
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,000
 from the hand of all those who hate us

286
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,000
 to show mercy to our ancestors,

287
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
 to remember his holy covenant,

288
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,000
 the oath he swore to our father Abraham,

289
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 to rescue us, to rescue us

290
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,000
 from the hands of our enemies."

291
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:03,000
 God's agenda is about saving people.

292
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:06,000
 It's about rescuing a lost people,

293
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:10,000
 a people in need of hope and in need of rest.

294
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:14,000
 See, this idea of salvation is a loaded, complex topic.

295
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,000
 Pastor Andrew broke into it last week

296
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 when he looked at Mary's song of salvation.

297
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,000
 But you have to understand, like he said,

298
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:24,000
 salvation to the Jews isn't,

299
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,000
 their first century Jewish people

300
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,000
 aren't thinking about the cross and eternity.

301
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
 They're actually just thinking about right now.

302
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,000
 Like we need salvation from this.

303
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,000
 This moment is hard.

304
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,000
 We need salvation from here.

305
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,000
 Salvation from our enemies.

306
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,000
 That was a package deal that came

307
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,000
 with some sensitive and deep expectations

308
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
 because the people had real enemies.

309
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:46,000
 They had been taken over by the Babylonians and destroyed,

310
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,000
 taken over by the Persians and exiled,

311
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,000
 now under foreign occupation by the Romans.

312
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:53,000
 They had needs.

313
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:56,000
 They needed saving.

314
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 And they'd been crying out for years.

315
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,000
 And so it's because of this reason

316
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,000
 they would start to see their salvation

317
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:05,000
 to mean the removal of the present struggle that I'm in,

318
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,000
 the current issue.

319
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,000
 That's what God's salvation.

320
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,000
 When they would hear this,

321
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
 they would think salvation means this.

322
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,000
 But actually the angel would mean something a little different.

323
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,000
 It's critical that we don't miss this.

324
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,000
 God's salvation has a bigger impact

325
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,000
 on our eternal condition

326
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:25,000
 than just the removal of our present trouble.

327
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,000
 I'm going to say that one more time.

328
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,000
 God's salvation has a bigger impact

329
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 on your eternal condition

330
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:37,000
 than just the removal of your current struggle.

331
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:40,000
 That's the salvation Zachariah is singing about.

332
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,000
 Salvation of the spiritual type.

333
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:46,000
 Salvation through the removal of the threat

334
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:50,000
 that anything or anyone can ever pose on you

335
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 and make you prisoner to or subject to.

336
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 That salvation is an eternal rest.

337
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 It's a long-term thing.

338
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:03,000
 God has kept his promise and he offers us that salvation,

339
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:07,000
 changing the trajectory of you and my eternity.

340
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,000
 Playing a long game,

341
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,000
 putting us in position

342
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,000
 to choose an eternity of rest with him,

343
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 of shalom,

344
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,000
 which means we're able to navigate

345
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,000
 through the situations we're in currently.

346
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:23,000
 See, we can work through just about anything,

347
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,000
 just about anything,

348
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 when we know that we've been saved

349
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
 and that there is an eternal rest for us.

350
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:34,000
 When we know how the book ends,

351
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,000
 we read it more confidently.

352
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,000
 And the story ends.

353
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:41,000
 What salvation would mean is that the story ends

354
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:44,000
 with God rescuing us forever

355
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,000
 and us being with him

356
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:50,000
 in that type of eternal rest.

357
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,000
 See, God brings about a salvation

358
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,000
 affecting the condition of the soul,

359
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 shifting humanity's eternal position

360
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 and restoring us back to him.

361
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:05,000
 God's salvation isn't temporary,

362
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,000
 but our temporary current struggles are.

363
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,000
 And that's something to really think about.

364
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,000
 The salvation he's offering us through this

365
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:14,000
 isn't gonna burn out,

366
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,000
 isn't gonna stop working,

367
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,000
 isn't gonna grow old,

368
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:20,000
 isn't gonna fail and wither.

369
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,000
 But the current tensions that we sit in,

370
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:25,000
 the current struggles of today

371
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,000
 may only last today,

372
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,000
 may only last this year.

373
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,000
 See, God's salvation changes our perspective

374
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 on what's eternal and what's not.

375
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:38,000
 His salvation makes sure that our eternity

376
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,000
 can be filled with rest.

377
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,000
 It's an eternity of restoration,

378
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,000
 an eternity of shalom.

379
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,000
 That eternity is promised to us,

380
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 and it's something like this,

381
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
 where our tears are wiped away,

382
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,000
 where there's no more shame,

383
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,000
 where no more weeping,

384
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:57,000
 no more sorrow, no more death,

385
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,000
 where we're no longer striving,

386
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:04,000
 where we're no longer thwarted by our enemies,

387
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,000
 to where fear and death can no longer alter

388
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:10,000
 who we're called and who we're meant to be.

389
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,000
 This is the eternal rest that God's mission,

390
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:15,000
 God's salvation is speaking to.

391
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:19,000
 This is what Zachariah is singing about.

392
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:22,000
 In Advent, this season that we're in,

393
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,000
 is the starting point.

394
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,000
 It's when God steps into the world

395
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:30,000
 and begins his plan of salvation.

396
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:33,000
 It's where the rubber would meet the road.

397
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:36,000
 And I think it's seeing this and understanding this,

398
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:39,000
 that Zachariah is possessed with song,

399
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:42,000
 to where as soon as he gets a chance to,

400
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,000
 he sings praises to God,

401
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:46,000
 because God has come to rescue us,

402
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:50,000
 to bring us salvation.

403
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,000
 Regardless of our trouble,

404
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:55,000
 God comes and he offers you and me

405
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:59,000
 a salvation that goes beyond just today,

406
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:03,000
 goes beyond just the temporary obstacles that we can see,

407
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:07,000
 a salvation that covers all.

408
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:14,000
 He comes to offer us an eternal rest.

409
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:18,000
 Zachariah wraps up his passage,

410
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,000
 his song, his singing,

411
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:24,000
 by hitting on a really big topic about rest,

412
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:29,000
 which kind of is a bit of the big story of scripture.

413
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:32,000
 From both Genesis all the way to Revelation,

414
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:35,000
 we see this concept woven in between the stories

415
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:38,000
 and the principles and the precepts.

416
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:40,000
 The very last line of this passage says this,

417
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:43,000
 "To enable us to serve him without fear,

418
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,000
 "in holiness and righteousness,

419
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:50,000
 "before him all of our days."

420
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,000
 Without fear.

421
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:55,000
 It's a beautiful condition

422
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:58,000
 and a hard thing for us to step into.

423
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 See, for all of human history,

424
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,000
 from Genesis 3 onward,

425
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,000
 there's been this continual pursuit

426
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,000
 to regain what was lost,

427
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,000
 and what was lost.

428
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 It was a space where humanity could live without fear,

429
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:15,000
 could live full and live whole.

430
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,000
 That was the Garden of Eden,

431
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:20,000
 a state of all perfect harmony.

432
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,000
 It's promised again in Revelation chapter 22.

433
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:26,000
 We see Eden restored,

434
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:29,000
 so that all of us, all of creation,

435
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,000
 can enter once again into this rest

436
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:36,000
 that comes without fear.

437
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,000
 The people of God would spend the majority of their time

438
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,000
 chasing after this,

439
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,000
 a rest that looks like a freedom from their enemies,

440
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:44,000
 a restoration and a peace.

441
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:47,000
 I think it's because rest looks like the existence,

442
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,000
 our existence without fear,

443
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,000
 it makes it really easy for the people

444
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:53,000
 to see what Zachariah is talking about

445
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:56,000
 and to see that the only way that's possible

446
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:58,000
 is if they were in a specific situation

447
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,000
 or if things looked a certain way.

448
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,000
 For them, if they were in their land with no oppressors,

449
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,000
 then they had no reason to be afraid.

450
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 So they started seeing rest based off of their land,

451
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,000
 based off of their circumstance.

452
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,000
 Their rest had become dependent

453
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:17,000
 on things going a certain way,

454
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,000
 on the stability of their land,

455
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,000
 on the way that their country was set up,

456
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,000
 on what they deemed necessary

457
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 to actually enter into rest.

458
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,000
 All the while, God is promising to send a Messiah

459
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,000
 who's going to come and set the captives free,

460
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,000
 but in their situation,

461
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:31,000
 they still have all this oppression,

462
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 so how can they be at rest?

463
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:38,000
 The people were looking for God

464
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:42,000
 to come and shift a geopolitical landscape.

465
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:46,000
 They were looking for him to come and change the settings

466
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,000
 and the conditions of their land.

467
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:51,000
 God was actually coming to change the settings

468
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,000
 and the conditions of their heart.

469
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:57,000
 See, they were looking in the wrong place.

470
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,000
 They were missing it.

471
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,000
 And I think we too can find ourselves

472
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,000
 weary and exhausted and restless

473
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:08,000
 when we spend our time looking for a good thing,

474
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,000
 looking for the right thing,

475
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:12,000
 but in the wrong place.

