 (audience laughs)

507
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,000
 That's not really how the story was supposed to go.

508
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:12,000
 So I'm like, "Okay, fine, it must be in my pocket."

509
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,000
 Because I do make that mistake every so often.

510
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,000
 I put something where it doesn't belong.

511
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,000
 My wife gets on to me quite a lot about it, and she's right.

512
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,000
 And this was a great example of it.

513
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,000
 So I'm like, "You know what?

514
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:22,000
 "If it's not in my AirPods, maybe it's in my pocket."

515
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:25,000
 So I start searching my pocket, searching my back pocket.

516
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,000
 I have a jacket on, so I'm searching that pocket.

517
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,000
 That has another pocket inside.

518
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:31,000
 I'm searching every possible pocket that's available,

519
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,000
 and there's no AirPods in them.

520
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:34,000
 And I'm starting to get pretty annoyed

521
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:37,000
 and pretty frustrated and pretty restless

522
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,000
 because all I need to really hit that zone

523
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:42,000
 of me and God in this sermon is some good music,

524
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,000
 and I'm so close.

525
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:44,000
 I've got my phone,

526
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,000
 but I can't just play it loud.

527
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,000
 It's not gonna work.

528
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:51,000
 So it hits me.

529
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:52,000
 I just don't have my AirPods,

530
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:54,000
 so I guess I have to go back home.

531
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:58,000
 So frustrated promise is just walking back,

532
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:02,000
 moping head down, pretty frustrated,

533
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:06,000
 uttering all sorts of ridiculousness under his breath.

534
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:13,000
 And I--like, my ears feel funny.

535
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:17,000
 So I take my hand, and I do this.

536
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,000
 And guess where my AirPods were.

537
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,000
 [laughter]

538
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,000
 Silly.

539
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:25,000
 It's sitting right in my ears.

540
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:29,000
 I had gone through this whole range of emotion

541
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:31,000
 because my AirPods were in my ears.

542
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:35,000
 But how often is that the case with us,

543
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:41,000
 where we're looking for something in the wrong place?

544
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:43,000
 What does that do to us spiritually

545
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:47,000
 when we look for rest in the wrong place?

546
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:50,000
 That's the very source of our restlessness.

547
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:52,000
 Can I break it down for us?

548
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:55,000
 Rest isn't gonna be found in a nation or in a country

549
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:57,000
 or in a virus-free world.

550
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:00,000
 It's not gonna be found in a better bank account statement.

551
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:03,000
 It's not gonna be found in--name it.

552
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:08,000
 That rest isn't situational or circumstantial.

553
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:10,000
 And when we seek these circumstances,

554
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:12,000
 maybe a better strategy,

555
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:14,000
 maybe a better 2022 list of goals,

556
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,000
 then I'll be at rest.

557
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:19,000
 You won't enter into lasting rest that way.

558
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:21,000
 It's not how it was designed.

559
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:25,000
 No, rest couldn't be found in the land for the Jewish people

560
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:28,000
 because it was never in the land.

561
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,000
 Rest is salvific.

562
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,000
 It's based off of salvation,

563
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:36,000
 off of something that only God can offer us,

564
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:38,000
 a restoration of what is broken.

565
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:42,000
 Rest is the releasing of our extraneous efforts

566
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:44,000
 to earn God's favor.

567
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:48,000
 It's God ridding us of having to live in fear of our sin,

568
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:52,000
 of our enemies, of anything.

569
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:55,000
 Rest is the state where the condition of our world

570
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:58,000
 doesn't distort our holiness or righteousness,

571
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:03,000
 but rather we are free to serve him and to know him.

572
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,000
 This is Zachariah's song.

573
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 This is, like, the pinnacle of what he's saying.

574
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:13,000
 Free from fear, what rest really looks like.

575
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:17,000
 So we get weary looking for rest in all the wrong places,

576
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,000
 like I was looking for my AirPods in all the wrong places.

577
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:22,000
 So I guess the logical question is where do you actually look?

578
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:24,000
 Where is the right place?

579
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:27,000
 Cool, you've listed nine places, promise, where I can't find rest.

580
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,000
 Give me one place where I can find it.

581
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:30,000
 Thank you for asking that question.

582
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:35,000
 I will give you one place.

583
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:41,000
 Rest is only found in what we celebrate in this Advent season.

584
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:43,000
 That's why this passage is here.

585
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:47,000
 See, Advent is the anticipation, the longing, the waiting,

586
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:50,000
 and the receiving of Jesus Christ.

587
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:55,000
 Born in a manger in a most humble of positions,

588
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:58,000
 that's actually where we're going to find our rest.

589
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:01,000
 It's not going to be in the state of things.

590
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:04,000
 It's going to be in him.

591
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:08,000
 Rest would be a baby born in a manger.

592
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:11,000
 Rest would be Jesus who grew up and would say

593
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,000
 one of the most beautiful things in scripture.

594
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:16,000
 He would say this, "Come to me."

595
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:21,000
 He's calling, "Come unto me, all of you who are weary,

596
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:25,000
 "heavy laden, restless," use whatever translation you want.

597
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:33,000
 "If you've got stuff, come to me, and I will give you rest."

598
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:36,000
 Not, "I will tell you where to go to get rest."

599
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 "I won't give you money, that'll give you rest."

600
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 "I won't give you a more perfect land, and that'll give you rest."

601
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,000
 No, "I'll give you me."

602
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:48,000
 The idea is this, rest can only be found in Jesus.

603
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:53,000
 That's because rest is not a place, it's a person.

604
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:56,000
 Jesus won't point you somewhere to find your rest.

605
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:58,000
 No, he'll say, "Come, follow me.

606
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,000
 "If you've got stuff, that's okay.

607
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:02,000
 "Come to me, all of you who are weary,

608
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 "all of you who are in chains, and I will give you rest."

609
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:10,000
 Rest without fear, rest that allows you to serve him

610
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:13,000
 in holiness and in righteousness, free from fear.

611
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 And wouldn't we love that?

612
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:19,000
 That's the reason Zachariah sings.

613
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:21,000
 That's the reason Jesus comes to earth.

614
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:24,000
 That's the reason we celebrate Advent.

615
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 We, his people, celebrate the remembering of a God

616
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:29,000
 who keeps promises.

617
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:32,000
 His promise still stands.

618
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,000
 A God whose plan to save us is not just to save us

619
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:37,000
 from today and today's troubles,

620
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:41,000
 but has a longer, bigger picture, bigger than we think.

621
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 Man, the worship set was right on, guys.

622
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 Well done.

623
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:51,000
 Advent is a season calling us, those of us who are restless,

624
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:55,000
 those of us who are weary, to come and follow him,

625
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 because that's how we're going to find our rest.

626
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,000
 That's the only way we can live, free from fear,

627
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:04,000
 free from the bondage that sin and that life can put on us.

628
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:08,000
 So here's my pitch, here's the thing.

629
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:13,000
 I know we're tired, I'm tired, it's been a hard year for me too.

630
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,000
 I'm exhausted.

631
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:17,000
 A lot of us here at the Vine are actually weary,

632
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 we're actually restless.

633
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:23,000
 We can't make a light of the challenges that the people

634
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:27,000
 in Hong Kong have faced in the past two years.

635
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 People around the world are facing with this virus.

636
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:32,000
 And because of those challenges,

637
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:36,000
 it might seem like rest is impossible.

638
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:38,000
 It might seem like if rest exists,

639
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:42,000
 it might just be right out of my reach.

640
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:45,000
 And what we so desperately need is a kind of rest

641
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:49,000
 that allows us to remember that God keeps his promise,

642
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,000
 a rest that then brings a confidence to us.

643
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:55,000
 What us weary people need is a rest that shows us the eternal,

644
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,000
 the big picture of what God is doing,

645
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:58,000
 even when we can't see it,

646
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:01,000
 even when our situation hasn't changed right before our eyes,

647
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:06,000
 what he's doing internally and eternally.

648
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,000
 A rest that will combat our fears,

649
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:12,000
 delivering us from the threat and the hold and the grip

650
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:15,000
 that our enemies, that our sin, that our shame,

651
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:18,000
 that our insecurities have on us,

652
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 and render their impact as ineffective against our soul.

653
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 So maybe you're here today and you fall into that category.

654
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 Maybe you would say my life feels like,

655
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 characterized by incessant fear.

656
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:37,000
 Maybe it's fear of the future,

657
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 fear of this next wave of the virus,

658
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,000
 fear of not being fully in control of your life,

659
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 fear of not getting the job that you wanted,

660
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:51,000
 just name it.

661
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:54,000
 All of those impact us and take a toll on us,

662
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:57,000
 but the good news today is that in Jesus,

663
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:01,000
 we can be free from those fears.

664
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:05,000
 He can show us how to live without those things

665
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 distorting our view, without those things oppressing us,

666
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:14,000
 without those things breaking us down from the inside.

667
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 So if you're tired and you're weary,

668
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 if you're broken, if you're hopeless,

669
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:23,000
 if you got stuff, that's okay.

670
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:27,000
 He doesn't say only come to me if you're perfect.

671
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 He says come to me if you're tired.

672
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,000
 If you're weary, great, come to me.

673
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:32,000
 If you're restless, okay, come to me.

674
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 If you've got a bunch of stuff, come to me.

675
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
 And in that coming to him, there's this beautiful exchange.

676
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:41,000
 Where God actually swaps some things.

677
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:46,000
 See, he takes your burden, he takes your shame,

678
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:48,000
 the things that are holding you,

679
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:51,000
 that are freezing you from being who you're meant to be,

680
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 the fear that we can live in, he actually takes that.

681
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:59,000
 And in place of that, he gives you something else.

682
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:02,000
 He gives you his rest, and that rest

683
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:05,000
 is what allows us to walk daily with him.

684
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:08,000
 It shows up in things like courage when we don't have it,

685
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:13,000
 strength when we feel weak, hope when all seems lost.

686
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:17,000
 All these fruit of the spirit, self-control and patience

687
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:20,000
 and gentleness when things aren't gentle around us.

688
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:24,000
 That's what entering into his rest can do for us.

689
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:28,000
 When we exchange what we have for what he is,

690
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:31,000
 he allows these things to bud in us,

691
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:35,000
 bringing us into a space where we can be full of rest,

692
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:40,000
 free from fear, and in wholeness.

693
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:44,000
 May this Advent season lead us into a place

694
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:47,000
 of deeper rest with Christ,

695
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:50,000
 born unto us so that we will know him

696
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:53,000
 and that we will know rest.

697
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:56,000
 Let's stand and we'll pray.

698
00:35:56,000 --> 00:36:01,000
 (pages rustling)

699
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:05,000
 God, your words are true.

700
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 Your words are good, and your words say

701
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:11,000
 that you keep your word, you keep your promise.

702
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:13,000
 So God, we just come before you today

703
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:17,000
 as people with various things on our heart,

704
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:22,000
 various things that impact who we are.

705
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:25,000
 And we come to a promise keeping God,

706
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:27,000
 knowing that if you did it then,

707
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:31,000
 if you kept your word then, you'll keep your word to us.

708
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:34,000
 God, we thank you for Advent.

709
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:37,000
 We thank you for Jesus coming and being with us.

710
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,000
 We thank you that your plan for our salvation

711
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:42,000
 isn't just for right now.

712
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:46,000
 God, thank you that you care about tomorrow as well.

713
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:50,000
 Thank you that your plan is well thought of.

714
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:54,000
 And God, we find ourselves in this space of restlessness

715
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:58,000
 when we seek after sometimes good things,

716
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:02,000
 but in the wrong places.

717
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:05,000
 God, some of us are tired looking for good things

718
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:07,000
 in the wrong places and not finding it.

719
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:09,000
 And I just pray, Lord, that your spirit

720
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,000
 will come and minister to us,

721
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:15,000
 will redirect our efforts,

722
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:18,000
 not to a thing, not to a location,

723
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:21,000
 not to a setting or a circumstance, Lord,

724
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:25,000
 but through your spirit, will you turn our eyes,

725
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,000
 shift our perspective,

726
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:33,000
 and allow us to follow you more closely.

727
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:37,000
 And God, we ask for your rest.

728
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:40,000
 We know that you know what it's been like.

729
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:43,000
 We know because you came and you have felt it all

730
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:47,000
 and you've walked in oppression and you've been there.

731
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:49,000
 And so God, from the sin that entangles us,

732
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:52,000
 we ask for your rest.

733
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:55,000
 For the personal deep insecurities that plague us

734
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:57,000
 from being who you call us to be,

735
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:00,000
 we ask for your rest.

736
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:03,000
 For the brokenness in our homes and in our families,

737
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:06,000
 relationships where things just aren't as they're meant to be,

738
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:13,000
 we ask for your spirit and for your rest.

739
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:15,000
 May your presence come.

740
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:17,000
 May your spirit work in us, Lord.

741
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:20,000
 And may you lead us to a place

742
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:25,000
 where we can live in that rest that you so freely give.

743
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:29,000
 [music]

744
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:33,000
 [music]

